4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING THE POWERS AND DUTIES OF THE DEPARTMENT
5 OF CORRECTIONS; ALLOWING THE DEPARTMENT OF CORRECTIONS TO CONTRACT WITH PRIVATE
6 CORPORATIONS TO ESTABLISH AND MAINTAIN CERTAIN FACILITIES AND PROGRAMS; AND
7 AMENDING SECTION 53-1-203, MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 53-1-203, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "53-1-203. Powers and duties of department of corrections. (1) The department of corrections
13 shall:
14 (a) subject to subsection (6), adopt rules necessary:
15 (i) for the siting, establishment, and expansion of prerelease centers;
16 (ii) for the expansion of treatment facilities or programs previously established by contract through
17 a competitive procurement process;
18 (iii) for the establishment and maintenance of residential methamphetamine treatment programs;
19 and
20 (iv) for the admission, custody, transfer, and release of persons in department programs and state
21 prisons, as defined in 53-30-101, except as otherwise provided by law;
22 (b) subject to the functions of the department of administration, lease or purchase lands for use by
23 correctional facilities and classify those lands to determine those that may be most profitably used for
24 agricultural purposes, taking into consideration the needs of all correctional facilities for the food products that
25 can be grown or produced on the lands and the relative value of agricultural programs in the treatment or
26 rehabilitation of the persons confined in correctional facilities;
27 (c) contract with private, nonprofit Montana corporations or, pursuant to the Montana Community
28 Corrections Act, with community corrections facilities or programs or local or tribal governments to establish
