1 (k) maintain adequate data on placements that it funds in order to keep the legislature properly
2 informed of the specific information, by category, related to delinquent youth in out-of-home care facilities;
3 (l) provide funding for youth who are committed to the department for placement in a correctional
4 facility as defined in 41-5-103;
5 (m) administer correctional facilities as defined in 41-5-103; and
6 (n) use to maximum efficiency the resources of state government in a coordinated effort to:
7 (i) provide for delinquent youth committed to the department; and
8 (ii) coordinate and apply the principles of modern correctional administration to the facilities and
