10 (2) The department may contract with private, nonprofit or for-profit Montana corporations to
11 establish and maintain a residential sexual offender treatment program. If the department intends to contract for
12 that purpose, the department shall adopt rules for the establishment and maintenance of that program.
13 (3) The department and a private, nonprofit or for-profit Montana corporation may not enter into a
14 contract under subsection (1)(c) or (2) for a period that exceeds 20 years. The provisions of 18-4-313 that limit
15 the term of a contract do not apply to a contract authorized by subsection (1)(c) or (2). Prior to entering into a
16 contract for a period of 20 years, the department shall submit the proposed contract to the legislative audit
17 committee. The legislative audit division shall review the contract and make recommendations or comments to
18 the legislative audit committee. The committee may make recommendations or comments to the department.
19 The department shall respond to the committee, accepting or rejecting the committee recommendations or
20 comments prior to entering into the contract.
21 (4) The department of corrections may enter into contracts with nonprofit corporations or
22 associations or private organizations to provide substitute care for delinquent youth in correctional facilities.
23 (5) The department may contract with Montana corporations to operate a day reporting program as
24 an alternate sentencing option as provided in 46-18-201 and 46-18-225 and as a sanction option under 46-23-
25 1015. The department shall adopt by rule the requirements for a day reporting program, including but not
26 limited to requirements for daily check-in, participation in programs to develop life skills, and the monitoring of
27 compliance with any conditions of probation, such as drug testing.
28 (6) Rules adopted by the department pursuant to subsection (1)(a) may not amend or alter the
