1 statutory powers and duties of the state board of pardons and parole. The rules for the siting, establishment,
2 and expansion of prerelease centers must state that the siting is subject to any existing conditions, covenants,
3 restrictions of record, and zoning regulations. The rules must provide that a prerelease center may not be sited
4 at any location without community support. The prerelease siting, establishment, and expansion must be
5 subject to, and the rules must include, a reasonable mechanism for a determination of community support for or
6 objection to the siting of a prerelease center in the area determined to be impacted. The prerelease siting,
7 establishment, and expansion rules must provide for a public hearing conducted pursuant to Title 2, chapter 3.
8 (7) The department shall ensure that risk and needs assessments drive the department's
9 supervision and correctional practices, including integrating assessment results into supervision contact
10 standards and case management. The department shall regularly validate its risk assessment tool."
